  "title": "Admin Assistant [O&G MNC/WEST]",
  "description": "<p><strong>The Opportunity</strong></p><p>Adecco is partnering with an Oil and Gas Multinational Corporation company to search for an <strong>Admin Assistant.</strong></p><ul><li>Office location: West</li></ul><p><strong>The Talent</strong><br /></p><ul><li><p>At least <strong>2–3 years of administrative support experience</strong> in a professional setting</p></li><li><p>Comfortable engaging with <strong>diverse stakeholders</strong>, including internal teams and external partners</p></li><li><p>Strong organizational and multitasking abilities</p></li></ul><p><br /><strong>The Job</strong><br /></p><ul><li><p>Prepare, submit, and track <strong>expense claims, invoices, and time records</strong> in line with company policies</p></li><li><p>Organize and manage <strong>meeting arrangements and schedules</strong> for team groups</p></li><li><p>Support <strong>employee-related administrative processes</strong>, including maintaining organizational information and internal updates</p></li><li><p>Oversee <strong>office operations and logistical arrangements</strong> to ensure efficient workflow</p></li><li><p>Coordinate <strong>travel bookings and related arrangements</strong> when required</p></li><li><p>Execute and support <strong>shared administrative processes</strong> across teams or functions</p></li><li><p>Take on <strong>additional administrative tasks</strong> as assigned to meet business needs</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Next Step:</strong></h3><ul><li>Send your <strong>updated cv at JiaYi.Lim@adecco.com</strong></li><li><strong>Email Subject: Admin Assistant (O&G MNC/WEST)</strong></li><li>Only shortlisted candidates will be contacted</li></ul><p><br />Lim Jia Yi<br />EA License Number: 91C2918<br />Personnel Registration Number: R24119814</p>",
